===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# (''also'' '''[[filet]]''') A [[strip]] or [[compact]] [[piece]] of [[meat]] or [[fish]] from which any [[bone]]s have been [[remove]]d.
# (''architecture'') A thin flat [[moulding]]/[[molding]] used as [[separation]] between larger mouldings.
# A [[rounded]] [[relief]] or [[cut]] at an [[edge]], especially an inside edge, added for a finished appearance and to break sharp edges.  
<!--Is this actually "fillet weld"?
# A type of [[weld]] that creates a rounded [[bead]] at an inside corner.
#:''Place a '''fillet''' weld at the joint.''
-->

